        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 7:39PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 739 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lexa, or near St Francis National Park, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Helena-West Helena, St Francis National Park, Tunica, Lexa, Rondo,
Dubbs, Dundee, North Tunica, Lula, Lagrange, Jeffersonville,
Haleside, Quarles, Austin, Jeffries, Wycamp, Latour, Helena Crossing,
Cypress Corner, and Poplar Grove.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for
eastern Arkansas...and northwestern Mississippi.</instruction>
